deck: An abused teenager who remodels himself as a top gangster and commits various crimes across Marshville with his gang.
description:
Origin

Matthew is the son of Nicholas and Mary Blackstone. Nicholas owned and ran a bar in Marshville. After being transported to a prehistoric jungle, the town of Marshville was divided into two parts by an electric fence to keep out the dinosaurs. Nicholas' bar was on the other side of the fence. He was able to salvage most of the liquor. As a result, Nicholas and Mary spent most of their days drunk and abusing their son Matthew. After having his face sliced, Matthew ran away from home. To survive, he fashoined himself as a gangster, gathering other teenage criminals around him. One of his crimes resulted in the powering down of the electric fence, enabling dinosaurs to come into the inhabited parts of Marshville.
name: Matthew Blackstone

deck: Mort Fatale is the alien leader of The Dead Boys and enemy of Lobo.
description:
Mort Fatale is the criminal alien leader to the Dead Boys (Jugula, Bloodstain, Bloodshed and Kooty-Graz) who had several arrest warrants to vast planetary law enforcement agencies. His past is unknown beyond his likeness to Earth monsters and dresses like an 18th century undertaker. Operating on the corrupt, criminal Planet Vurkin under the control of the Pan-Galactic mob, Fatale schemed with mob accountant, Vernon J. Qigley, on a fake kidnapping-ransom of 100 million credits less Qigley would be turned into L.E.G.I.O.N. for his 10 million credit warrant for his shady accounts and his 20 year knowledge of illicit mob activities that would put the entire syndicate in prison.

Lobo unwittingly killed Fatale's getaway driver, Robert De Nitro, on an unrelated arrest warrant for unpaid alimony which lead to De Nitro's death after falling off a building from a botched escape. Upon returning to his bounty agent, Bunsen, for additional work was the opportunity to have Qigley's arrest warrant up in the air which Lobo set to collect with the assist of Jonas Glim.

On the corrupt Planet Vurkin, Mort Fatale fell into a back-up plan to dig Qigley through the sewers to avoid death and capture by law officials, the mob, or bounty hunters but not before eliminating several hired goons of the mob and sending their blackmail notice to the mob headquarters as well. Lobo would search the planet through bribed cops and bruising snitches to a series of warehouses only to intervene on an armored mob raid to take Qigley from Mort Fatale by force then go underground.

Lobo and Jonas Glim each would then intervene to overtake the Dead Boys each until an explosion by mob intervention caused the whole gang to drown in raw sewage but not until a double-cross intervention from Lobo's rival bounty hunter duo, Johnny Quietus and Murder, who were sent on Bunsen's behalf to ridicule Lobo and get a larger split of the bounty apart of Lobo's asking wage. Lobo would come to apprehend Vernon Qigley to escape off his SpazFrag666 Spacehog only to leave the planet. Jonas Glim would be left behind only to claim contempt for Lobo but a paltry 5000 credit warrant for the Dead Boys each whether they were alive or otherwise. Since then, Mort Fatale nor his crew have been seen in space or beyond as of now.

Powers/ Abilities: Mort Fatale is an alien resembling of earth-based ghouls who has the strength, speed, and extra stamina of an Earth man of his age, height, and weight who engages in moderate exercise. He is invulnerable to degrees to take a punch from Lobo who is known to battle Superman but is vulnerable to specific projectiles. He is skilled in criminal ingenuities and firearms plus leadership. Mort Fatale has an odd ability with his bad breath or "coffin breath" which can knock out opponents or in Lobo's case can gag him into nausea or suffocation less he passes out.

deck: Entrepreneur and founder of Eden, the eco-friendly community of tomorrow located in Lake Michigan.
description:
Origin

A brilliant young man attending Columbia University had grown to love fellow student Susan Storm. But as he watched, she fell in love with another man named Reed Richards. He would forever hate Richards for this.

In the shadows, he would plot against the Fantastic Four and grow quite wealthy and powerful. He would reveal later that he was known only as The Quiet Man, having forgotten his true name, using technology to change his appearance so he could gain power and persuasion. He joined many professions and became CEO of many companies under different guises.

Creation

The Quiet Man was created by James Robinson and artist Leonard Kirk. He first appeared in Fantastic Four #5 as Aiden Toliver. He first appeared as Cully Moore in Fantastic Four #8. He revealed himself as the Quiet Man in Fantastic Four #14.

Story Arcs

John Eden is the founder and developer of Eden, a revolutionary, eco-friendly city located in Lake Michigan. After the Fantastic Four was removed from the Baxter Building following an event blamed on the Four, Reed Richards was offered a position at Eden. He was given an assistant named Cully Moore.

It would soon be revealed however that Cully was indeed the mastermind. He killed the man posing as John Eden and captured Mr. Fantastic as well as the children of the Future Foundation. He teamed up with the Wizard and has a group of protectors posing as members of the Avengers from Franklin Richard's pocket dimension.

Powers & Abilities

The Quiet Man has a nanite-derived facial reconstructor that can change his appearance. He has used this technology to become many individuals and own many companies.

He possesses genius level intellect and over time has become vastly wealthy, giving him vast resources at his disposal.

deck: A botched clone of Thomas Edison contaminated with cockatiel DNA.
description:
History

The Inventor is a failed clone of famed inventor Thomas Edison who was mixed with cockatiel DNA. He convinces teenagers of the New Jersey area that their lives would be better suited as batteries for his machines. His plans are thwarted by Ms. Marvel.

Abilities

The Inventor possesses a genius level intellect and uses it to build large robots and battle suits. It is not specified if any of his cockatiel DNA gives him any extra abilities but he does possess a bird beak and a birds eyes which could offer some advantages.

deck: Speedster from the DC Multiverse as well as being a big comic book fan. Romantically involved with Justice 9 teammate Flashlight

His first contact with the multiverse was when Superdoom attacked Optiman, the Superman of earth-36 and killed him in spite of the help of the other heroes (Flashlight and Iron Knight, included).

His second contact with worlds beyond was when Thunderer recruited him and his boyfriend Flashlight to help to rescue Nix Uotan.

Red Racer is the resident comic book geek expert of Justice Incarnate.
